# Streaming with Tool Use: Implementation Guide

Great question — this is a common source of confusion. Let me break down how streaming works with tools and show you the practical patterns.

## How Streaming + Tool Use Works

When you enable `stream: true`, Claude streams content in real-time **including tool calls**. The key insight:

**Tool calls stream as they're generated**, but you still need to:
1. Collect the full tool call before executing it
2. Send tool results back to Claude
3. Continue streaming the final response

Here's the flow:

```
Client                          Claude API
  |
  |--stream: true, tools: [...]-->|
  |                                |
  |<--message_start-----------------| 
  |<--content_block_start (tool_use)| (Tool call streaming begins)
  |<--content_block_delta (input)---| (Parameters stream in)
  |<--content_block_delta (input)---| (More parameters...)
  |<--content_block_stop------------|
  |                                |
  | (You execute the tool)         |
  |                                |
  |--messages (with tool result)-->|
  |                                |
  |<--message_start (continued)-----|
  |<--content_block_start (text)---|
  |<--content_block_delta (text)---| (Final response streams)
  |<--message_stop-----------------|
```

## Implementation: TypeScript/JavaScript Example

Here's a complete implementation using the SDK:

```typescript
import Anthropic from "@anthropic-ai/sdk";

const client = new Anthropic();

async function streamWithTools(userMessage: string) {
  const tools: Anthropic.Tool[] = [
    {
      name: "web_search",
      description: "Search the web for information",
      input_schema: {
        type: "object",
        properties: {
          query: {
            type: "string",
            description: "Search query",
          },
        },
        required: ["query"],
      },
    },
    {
      name: "code_execution",
      description: "Execute Python code",
      input_schema: {
        type: "object",
        properties: {
          code: {
            type: "string",
            description: "Python code to execute",
          },
        },
        required: ["code"],
      },
    },
  ];

  const messages: Anthropic.MessageParam[] = [
    { role: "user", content: userMessage },
  ];

  // Keep looping until Claude stops using tools
  while (true) {
    console.log("\n--- Streaming response ---");

    const stream = await client.messages.stream({
      model: "claude-opus-4-6",
      max_tokens: 4096,
      tools,
      messages,
    });

    let stopReason = "";
    const toolUses: Array<{
      id: string;
      name: string;
      input: Record<string, unknown>;
    }> = [];

    // Consume the stream
    for await (const chunk of stream) {
      if (chunk.type === "content_block_start") {
        if (chunk.content_block.type === "tool_use") {
          console.log(`\n🔧 Tool call: ${chunk.content_block.name}`);
        } else if (chunk.content_block.type === "text") {
          console.log("\n📝 Response: ", { end: false });
        }
      }

      if (chunk.type === "content_block_delta") {
        if (chunk.delta.type === "text_delta") {
          // Stream text to user in real-time
          process.stdout.write(chunk.delta.text);
        } else if (chunk.delta.type === "input_json_delta") {
          // Tool input parameters are streaming in
          console.log(chunk.delta.partial_json, { end: false });
        }
      }

      if (chunk.type === "message_delta") {
        stopReason = chunk.delta.stop_reason || "";
      }
    }

    // Get the final message to extract tool calls
    const finalMessage = await stream.finalMessage();
    console.log("\n");

    // Extract all tool use blocks
    for (const block of finalMessage.content) {
      if (block.type === "tool_use") {
        toolUses.push({
          id: block.id,
          name: block.name,
          input: block.input as Record<string, unknown>,
        });
      }
    }

    // If Claude isn't calling tools, we're done
    if (stopReason !== "tool_use" || toolUses.length === 0) {
      break;
    }

    // Execute tools and collect results
    console.log(`\n⚙️  Executing ${toolUses.length} tool(s)...`);
    const toolResults: Anthropic.ToolResultBlockParam[] = [];

    for (const tool of toolUses) {
      let result: string;

      try {
        if (tool.name === "web_search") {
          result = await executeWebSearch(tool.input.query as string);
        } else if (tool.name === "code_execution") {
          result = await executeCode(tool.input.code as string);
        } else {
          result = "Unknown tool";
        }
      } catch (error) {
        result = `Error: ${error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error)}`;
      }

      console.log(`✅ ${tool.name}: ${result.substring(0, 100)}...`);

      toolResults.push({
        type: "tool_result",
        tool_use_id: tool.id,
        content: result,
      });
    }

    // Add assistant's response and tool results to messages
    messages.push({
      role: "assistant",
      content: finalMessage.content,
    });

    messages.push({
      role: "user",
      content: toolResults,
    });
  }
}

// Mock tool implementations
async function executeWebSearch(query: string): Promise<string> {
  // In production, call your web search API
  return `Search results for "${query}": [mock results]`;
}

async function executeCode(code: string): Promise<string> {
  // In production, use Claude's code execution tool or your own sandbox
  return `Code execution result: [output]`;
}

// Run it
streamWithTools("Search for Claude AI news and run some analysis");
```

## Key Patterns

### Pattern 1: Fine-Grained Tool Streaming (Recommended)

**Use this** if you want to show tool parameters as they arrive:

```typescript
for await (const chunk of stream) {
  if (chunk.type === "content_block_delta") {
    if (chunk.delta.type === "input_json_delta") {
      // Show partial JSON as it streams in
      updateToolCallUI(chunk.delta.partial_json);
    } else if (chunk.delta.type === "text_delta") {
      // Show text as it streams
      updateResponseUI(chunk.delta.text);
    }
  }
}
```

This is **GA (generally available)** — no beta header needed. Perfect for:
- Multi-tool workflows where you want to show which tools are being called
- UX where you display the reasoning in real-time

### Pattern 2: Programmatic Tool Calling (Reduce Round-Trips)

If you want Claude to **call tools without streaming back to the client**, use programmatic tool calling:

```typescript
// Pseudo-code pattern
const stream = await client.messages.stream({
  model: "claude-opus-4-6",
  max_tokens: 4096,
  tools,
  messages,
});

// Claude calls a tool; you execute it programmatically
for await (const chunk of stream) {
  if (chunk.type === "content_block_start" && 
      chunk.content_block.type === "tool_use") {
    // Execute the tool immediately (no round-trip to client)
    const result = await executeToolProgrammatically(
      chunk.content_block.name,
      chunk.content_block.input
    );

    // Feed result back into stream
    stream.addToolResult(chunk.content_block.id, result);
  }
}
```

